The article is an executive order issued by President Donald Trump on January 13, 2021. The order is related to national security and defense, specifically addressing the threat posed by the People's Republic of China's military-industrial complex. The order amends certain sections of a previous executive order (Executive Order 13959) that was issued on November 12, 2020, which aimed to address the threat from securities investments that finance Communist Chinese military companies. The amendments specify the conditions under which transactions to divest from securities held in Communist Chinese military companies are permitted, as well as the possession of such securities by United States persons. The order also amends the definitions of Communist Chinese military companies and transactions, and includes general provisions regarding implementation and applicability of the order.